5 Sec. 202. The appropriations under this part and part 1 are
6 subject to the management and budget act, 1984 PA 431, MCL 18.1101
7 to 18.1594.
8 Sec. 203. As used in this part and part 1:
9 (a) "AFIS" means the automated fingerprint identification
10 system.
11 (b) "CJIS" means Criminal Justice Information Systems.
12 (c) "Department" means the department of state police.
13 (d) "DHS" means the United States Department of Homeland
14 Security.
15 (e) "Director" means the director of the department.
16 (f) "DNA" means deoxyribonucleic acid.
17 (g) "DOJ" means the United States Department of Justice.
18 (h) "DOT" means the United States Department of
19 Transportation.
20 (i) "FTE" means full-time equated position in the classified
21 service of this state.
22 (j) "IDG" means interdepartmental grant.
23 (k) "LEIN" means the law enforcement information network.
24 (l) "MCOLES" means the Michigan commission on law enforcement
25 standards created in section 3 of the Michigan commission on law
26 enforcement standards act, 1965 PA 203, MCL 28.603.
27 (m) "SIGMA" means the statewide integrated governmental
28 management application.
29 (n) "SRMS" means the state records management system.
