4 Sec. 222. To the extent possible, the department shall not
5 expend appropriations under part 1 until all existing authorized
6 work project funds available for the same purposes are exhausted.
7 Sec. 223. Not later than 6 months after the state budget
8 office issues work project letters, the department shall submit an
9 annual report that summarizes all work project accounts. The report
10 must include all of the following:
11 (a) A list of all work project accounts.
12 (b) The status of all work project accounts, including amounts
13 expended, amounts encumbered, and available balances for each
14 account.
15 (c) The amount of funds that lapsed from any previously
16 designated work project accounts, the name and description of the
17 work project account, and the funds that received the lapsed
18 amounts.
19 Sec. 224. Total authorized appropriations from all sources
20 under part 1 for legacy costs for the fiscal year ending September
21 30, 2027 are estimated at $126,492,400.00. From this amount, total
22 appropriations for pension-related legacy costs for the department
23 are estimated at $99,258,100.00. Total appropriations for retiree
24 health care legacy costs for the department are estimated at
25 $27,234,300.00.
26 Sec. 225. Not later than April 1, the department shall provide
27 to the standard report recipients a copy of its annual strategic
28 plan prepared in compliance with section 363 of the management and
29 budget act, 1984 PA 431, MCL 18.1363. The plan must include the
STM S06116'26 (S-1) b0u6xa

