3 Sec. 226. The department shall report on any court settlement
4 that may require further legislative review of state statutory
5 programs or regulations.
6 Sec. 227. Not later than November 15, the department shall
7 disclose on a publicly accessible website private and other third-
8 party funds received by the department in the previous fiscal year.
9 The report must include the amount of funding received, the
10 specific source of funding received, the purpose for which funding
11 was expended, and the amount of any remaining funds. The report
12 must be submitted to the standard report recipients and to the
13 chairpersons of the senate and house appropriations committees.
14 Sec. 228. The department shall submit a biannual report on the
15 performance metrics cited or information required to be reported in
16 this part, reasons for nonachievement of metric targets, and
17 proposed corrective actions.
18 Sec. 229. (1) It is the intent of the legislature that the
19 department shall take all steps necessary to protect the data and
20 privacy of citizens who are not the focus of a departmental
21 investigation and to protect personal information from unauthorized
22 access or misuse. The protection required under this subsection
23 includes, but is not limited to, all of the following:
24 (a) Requiring vendors or service providers to protect data
25 shared with them.
26 (b) Ensuring that when personal data is collected, but no
27 longer utilized by the department, that reasonable steps be taken
28 to securely destroy records containing personal information when it
29 is to be discarded so that the information is rendered
STM S06116'26 (S-1) b0u6xa

20
1 indecipherable and is not sold for marketing or other purposes.
2 (2) The department shall provide written notification to any
3 data subject whose sensitive personal information is accessed or
4 acquired by an unauthorized person.
5 Sec. 230. (1) Within 30 days of enactment of this act, the
6 house and senate shall provide to the state budget office a jointly
7 agreed-upon list of legislatively directed spending items funded in
8 part 1 as defined in section 364 of the management and budget act,
9 1984 PA 431, MCL 18.1364. The list must include all information and
10 documents pertaining to the funded items as publicly disclosed in
11 accordance with sections 364 and 364a of the management and budget
12 act, 1984 PA 431, MCL 18.1364 and 18.1364a.
13 (2) In accordance with section 364(4) of the management and
14 budget act, 1984 PA 431, MCL 18.1364, the department or agency
15 administering the grant shall post a report in a publicly
16 accessible location on its website beginning March 15 of the
17 current fiscal year. The department or agency shall update the
18 report and shall post an updated report not later than June 15 of
19 the current fiscal year, and again not later than September 15 of
20 the current fiscal year. The department shall include in the report
21 the most comprehensive information the department has available at
22 the time of posting for grants awarded.
23 Sec. 231. (1) The department may accept monetary and
24 nonmonetary gifts, bequests, donations, contributions, or grants
25 from any private or public source to support, in whole or in part,
26 a departmental function or program. The department shall expend or
27 use the gifts, bequests, donations, contributions, or grants
28 accepted under this subsection for the purposes designated by the
29 private or public source, if the purpose is specified.
